// Sliding Window Technique Explanation:
//
// It is used to reduce the time complexity of problems involving 
// arrays or strings that require checking all contiguous subarrays/substrings.
// Instead of recalculating sums or properties again and again, 
// we "slide" a window (a subarray) over the input and update our calculations efficiently.
//
// Commonly used in:
// - Subarray sums
// - Longest substring without repeating characters
// - Maximum/minimum elements in a window
